    "The final phase commenced with the unveiling of the top 10 candidates and concluded in February 2023 when NIST selected the Ascon family after careful consideration, as outlined in NISTIR 8454 [38].",
    "Design Strategies of Lightweight CryptographyDesigning a lightweight cryptography algorithm is more complicated than it may seem at first glance in terms of security.",
    "Since we talk about \"lightweight\" primitives, there must be a way to define the weight of an algorithm.",
    "Primitive is determined by the amount of time and space resources required to run it.",
    "This weight can be measured in both software and hardware [39]."
